\[
\sqrt{\left(\frac12\right)^4+\left(\frac12-\left(\frac12\right)^2\right)^2}
= \sqrt{\frac1{16}+\left(\frac12-\frac14\right)^2}
= \sqrt{\frac1{16}+\left(\frac14\right)^2}
= \sqrt{\frac1{16}+\frac1{16}} = \sqrt{\frac2{16}} = \frac{\sqrt2}{4}.
\]

The integral term has factor \(2(y-2y^2)=2\left(\frac12-2\cdot\frac14\right)=2\left(\frac12-\frac12\right)=0\), so the integral is \(0\). Hence \(f'(\frac12)=\frac{\sqrt2}{4}>0\).
